commit_list.message:
A lot of improvements to the error handling.

* KeyErrors thrown by and inline class are no longer silenced.
* The error silencing now only silences the inlines, not the entire text. Oops!
* More consistent throwing of InlineUnrenderable errors.

commit_list.message:
Serve the input bundle from a url instead of in a script tag.

This prevents things from blowing up if the passed in scripts happen to contain the string "</script>".

This also spits up node integration slightly because it wants a full html page.

While at it I switched to storing the source url in an actual temp file unless needed to be in-directory for node integration.
